      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0004",
      "text": " Specifies the EVFP message that is to be transmitted from the source to the",
      "bbox": [
        198.54,
        57.65,
        539.99,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0005",
      "text": "destination. The defined EVFP message codes are shown in table 117.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        69.65,
        410.37,
        80.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0006",
      "text": "Transaction Identifier:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        214.97,
        201.18,
        226.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0007",
      "text": " Uniquely identifies an EVFP transaction between two entities. The Transac-",
      "bbox": [
        201.18,
        214.97,
        540.07,
        226.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0008",
      "text": "tion Identifier shall be set by the EVFP Initiator, and each subsequent EVFP message shall contain",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        226.97,
        539.9,
        238.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0009",
      "text": "the same value, until the EVFP transaction is completed.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        238.97,
        346.48,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0010",
      "text": "NOTE 7 – The usage of the Transaction Identifier is very similar to the usage of an OX_ID when an Exchange",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        263.17,
        539.93,
        273.22
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0011",
      "text": "Originator is enforcing uniqueness via the OX_ID mechanism (see FC-FS-2), but it is not related in any way to",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        274.15,
        539.97,
        284.2
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0012",
      "text": "the OX_ID present in the Fibre Channel frames carrying the EVFP messages.",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        285.2,
        414.2,
        295.24
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0013",
      "text": "Core N_Port_Name / Core Switch_Name:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        310.97,
        289.07,
        322.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0014",
      "text": " If the originating FC_Port is an N_Port, this field shall be",
      "bbox": [
        289.2,
        310.97,
        539.88,
        322.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0015",
      "text": "set to its Core N_Port_Name. If the originating FC_Port is an F_Port, this field shall be set to the Core",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        322.97,
        539.96,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p130_s0016",
